Totally fair ‚Äî here's a breakdown of how you can do it for cheap (or free), and when it might start costing you something:

üí∏ COST BREAKDOWN (OpenAI + Hosting + Tools)
‚úÖ 1. OpenAI API (chatbot brain)
Model	Free?	Notes
gpt-3.5-turbo	‚úÖ Yes (if under $5/month usage)	Around $0.0015 per request (super cheap)
gpt-4	‚ùå Paid only	$0.03+ per message ‚Äî not worth it yet for basic Q&A
üí° Use gpt-3.5-turbo ‚Äî you can get hundreds of chats per month under $1.

‚úÖ 2. Framer Site (chat widget placement)
Plan	Cost	Notes
Free Plan	‚úÖ Free	Framer lets you publish simple sites for free
Pro Plan	$5‚Äì$20/mo	Only needed if you want custom domains or extra hosting
üí° You can run your chatbot inside a free Framer site with no problem.

‚úÖ 3. Backend API (Optional, but best practice)
If you don‚Äôt want to expose your OpenAI key in the frontend, you should use a free backend like:

üîπ Vercel serverless functions ‚Äì Free up to 100GB/month

üîπ Replit ‚Äì Free hosting with Node.js backend

üîπ Cloudflare Workers ‚Äì Free tier with generous limits

üí° Free tiers are enough for small portfolios or prototypes.

‚úÖ 4. Data Source / Embedding (if needed)
If your site is small, use a simple JavaScript object or JSON (free).

If you want smart search across your content, you'll need vector search (RAG) ‚Äî here‚Äôs how to do it affordably:

üîπ Supabase Vector ‚Äì Free tier

üîπ Pinecone ‚Äì Free for up to 1M vector storage

But for now, you don't need this if your content is structured.

‚úÖ Summary: What's Free vs Paid
Feature	Free	Cost Later?
Framer site	‚úÖ	Only if you need custom domain
Chat UI (React/JS)	‚úÖ	‚Äì
OpenAI GPT-3.5 API	‚úÖ	After $5/month usage
Backend (Replit/Vercel)	‚úÖ	‚Äì
Vector DB (optional)	‚úÖ	Only for complex sites
üí∞ Realistic Estimate for a Basic Portfolio Bot
MVP version (basic Q&A using GPT-3.5) = $0 to $1/month

Full version with embeddings + GPT-4 = $5 to $20/month

