Perfect! Since you're going with OpenAI‚Äôs GPT-3.5 API (which easily stays under $5/month for light usage) and building the UI in Framer using its built-in code component, here's a step-by-step guide to get your smart chatbot running on your website:

‚úÖ OVERVIEW
You‚Äôll build a chatbot in Framer that:

Uses a clean chat UI (text input + chat log)

Sends messages to OpenAI‚Äôs GPT-3.5 API

Receives a response based on your predefined content (like ‚ÄúWho is Panth?‚Äù, ‚ÄúTell me your experience‚Äù, etc.)

üîß STEP 1: Create Your Data (Panth Info)
You‚Äôll feed this into GPT so it only answers based on your site, not the internet.

const siteData = `
Panth Shah is a UX/Product Designer based in Mountain View. He has over 2 years of experience building AI-powered design systems and interfaces. He's worked at Founderway.AI, Northeastern University, and Boston New Technology.

He has completed 3 major case studies:
1. FounderMatch ‚Äì an AI co-founder matching platform
2. Phealth ‚Äì a nutrition and accessibility-focused app
3. Northeastern Student Hub ‚Äì redesigned for better accessibility and navigation

Panth specializes in accessibility, design systems, and building end-to-end UX flows for startups.
`;
üß† STEP 2: Get Your OpenAI API Key
Go to https://platform.openai.com/account/api-keys

Click Create new secret key

Save it somewhere safe (you‚Äôll use it in the backend, not directly in Framer)

üåê STEP 3: Create a Free Backend on Vercel
Create a small serverless function that handles the OpenAI API call so your key is safe.

Create a free account on Vercel.com

Create a new project (select "Hobby" plan ‚Äî free)

Add an API function like this:

// api/chat.js
export default async function handler(req, res) {
  const { message } = req.body;

  const prompt = `
You are an assistant that answers questions only about Panth Shah's portfolio. Here's the info:
${siteData}

User: ${message}
Answer:
`;

  const response = await fetch("https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions", {
    method: "POST",
    headers: {
      "Content-Type": "application/json",
      Authorization: `Bearer ${process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY}`,
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      model: "gpt-3.5-turbo",
      messages: [{ role: "user", content: prompt }],
    }),
  });

  const data = await response.json();
  res.status(200).json({ reply: data.choices[0].message.content });
}
Store your OpenAI API key in OPENAI_API_KEY via Vercel's Environment Variables

Deploy and get your endpoint URL, e.g.
https://your-project.vercel.app/api/chat

üß© STEP 4: Build the Chat UI in Framer
Use the Code Component inside Framer:

import * as React from "react";
import { Frame, addPropertyControls, ControlType } from "framer";

export function ChatBot() {
  const [messages, setMessages] = React.useState([]);
  const [input, setInput] = React.useState("");

  const sendMessage = async () => {
    if (!input.trim()) return;
    const newMessages = [...messages, { role: "user", text: input }];
    setMessages(newMessages);
    setInput("");

    const res = await fetch("https://your-vercel-url.vercel.app/api/chat", {
      method: "POST",
      headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
      body: JSON.stringify({ message: input }),
    });
    const data = await res.json();
    setMessages([...newMessages, { role: "assistant", text: data.reply }]);
  };

  return (
    <div style={{ padding: 20, width: "100%", fontFamily: "sans-serif" }}>
      <div style={{ maxHeight: 300, overflowY: "auto" }}>
        {messages.map((msg, i) => (
          <div key={i} style={{ margin: "10px 0" }}>
            <b>{msg.role === "user" ? "You" : "Bot"}:</b> {msg.text}
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <input
        style={{ width: "80%", padding: 8, marginTop: 10 }}
        value={input}
        onChange={(e) => setInput(e.target.value)}
        placeholder="Ask something..."
      />
      <button style={{ padding: 8, marginLeft: 10 }} onClick={sendMessage}>
        Send
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}
üéØ STEP 5: Test and Launch
Preview it inside Framer

Deploy your site

Try asking: ‚ÄúWho is Panth?‚Äù, ‚ÄúWhat are your projects?‚Äù, etc.

üîê Bonus: Add Rate Limit (Optional but Good)
To avoid spam:

Limit each IP to 50 messages/day (can be done in backend)

Add a delay/disable send button after a message

