üîß In a Next.js project, here‚Äôs what you do:
1. Create an API Route
Inside your Next.js project, make a file at:

/pages/api/chat.js
Paste this full working code üëá (OpenAI v4 compatible):

import OpenAI from "openai";

const openai = new OpenAI({
  apiKey: process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY,
});

const siteData = `YOUR FULL SITEDATA GOES HERE`;

export default async function handler(req, res) {
  if (req.method !== "POST") {
    return res.status(405).json({ message: "Method not allowed" });
  }

  const { message } = req.body;

  try {
    const chatCompletion = await openai.chat.completions.create({
      model: "gpt-3.5-turbo",
      messages: [
        { role: "system", content: siteData },
        { role: "user", content: message },
      ],
      temperature: 0.6,
    });

    const reply = chatCompletion.choices[0].message.content;
    res.status(200).json({ reply });
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Error calling OpenAI:", error);
    res.status(500).json({ error: "Failed to get response" });
  }
}
2. Set your API Key
In your root .env.local file, add:

OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
Restart your dev server after this.

3. Deploy to Vercel
Push your Next.js project to GitHub ‚Üí Connect to Vercel ‚Üí Done.
Make sure to add the same OPENAI_API_KEY in Vercel‚Äôs Environment Variables.

Once deployed, you‚Äôll get a URL like:

https://your-portfolio.vercel.app/api/chat
Use this URL inside your Framer code component to send requests.

